Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.42,0:00:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This jam is truly delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.85,0:00:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the local homemade cowberry jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.35,0:00:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, homemade?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.14,0:00:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told to show this to any customer who enjoys the jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.77,0:00:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who made this jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.90,0:00:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so he's the one who made this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Konrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.40,0:00:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a place on the hill to the south where\Nyou can pick a lot of cowberries.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.33,0:00:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, he ended up owning the whole area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.54,0:00:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And no one complained about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.25,0:00:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since his jam is so delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.84,0:00:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he is a very enjoyable man to be around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.80,0:00:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is one of the few people I call a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.30,0:00:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was his idea to show his photograph, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.51,0:00:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's his way of asking people\Nto support his cowberry jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.81,0:01:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we must come here again for this jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.56,0:01:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.86,0:01:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll be happy to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.65,0:03:00.78,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(313,200)\pos(363,337)}A Peaceful Home
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.46,0:02:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they really going to invade this peaceful town?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.80,0:03:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Invade?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.30,0:03:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are other methods than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a case where a single\Ngun destroyed an entire town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.19,0:03:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was in 1958, in Zweifelstadt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.27,0:03:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A series of murders occurred in Niedersachsen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.82,0:03:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the people began to suspect their\Nneighbors of being the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the townspeople became paranoid\Nabout even dull, everyday activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a state of mass hysteria...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.99,0:03:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one of the townspeople used a gun\Nhe purchased for "protection"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.25,0:03:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and shot his neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.17,0:03:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one could stop it after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The town was set on fire...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.55,0:03:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and everything within reach became a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.63,0:03:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The residents killed each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and no one survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.72,0:03:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.97,0:03:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that going to happen to this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.89,0:03:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to stop something like that before it starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may have already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.70,0:04:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, give me your money!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.16,0:04:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you have some!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and give it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.83,0:04:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that money is for...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.50,0:04:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's to buy alcohol for your drunk dad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.92,0:04:19.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drinking too much is bad for his health!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.67,0:04:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're helping him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.26,0:04:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's go eat at the usual place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.48,0:04:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.61,0:04:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hate them, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.11,0:04:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you hate them so much that you want to kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.87,0:04:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to talk to Konrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.67,0:04:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.67,0:04:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we went to the coffee shop just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't you notice how the owner, Ralph,\Nand all the customers were looking at us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.84,0:05:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because they don't see us together that often.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.47,0:05:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what they'll do if they learn we won\N20 million marks in the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.35,0:05:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.98,0:05:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that if we're going to be this paranoid...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.19,0:05:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'll be better if we just talk to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.98,0:05:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's true that Mr. Konrad might\Nknow that I won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.95,0:05:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.24,0:05:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if we pay him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.83,0:05:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll keep him quiet that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if Konrad is greedy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he keeps demanding money from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.25,0:05:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-When that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.76,0:05:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.85,0:05:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this the place where he comes to pick his cowberries?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.10,0:05:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.36,0:06:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Konrad isn't a bad person, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.24,0:06:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't the type of person...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who would ruin the happiness we've finally found, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.41,0:06:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, honey...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.92,0:06:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.72,0:06:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.80,0:06:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.30,0:06:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l-lt wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.56,0:06:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What have you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, it wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.19,0:06:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who would do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.98,0:06:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How should I know!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.10,0:06:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't used the gun since I bought it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.11,0:06:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, shut up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.66,0:06:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That dog pisses me off...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.95,0:06:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, this is irritating...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be in a very good mood today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.84,0:07:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something good happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.30,0:07:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He finally showed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.13,0:07:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who showed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.05,0:07:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wonderful man who will take\Nme away from this town!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.15,0:07:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.65,0:07:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.32,0:07:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire town...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.82,0:07:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is laughing at me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.82,0:07:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! This is stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.09,0:07:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.50,0:07:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.27,0:07:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is this, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.65,0:08:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your son has already taken one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.62,0:08:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.62,0:08:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the dog stopped barking...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.39,0:08:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.26,0:08:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.81,0:08:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Lipsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Franz Bonaparta's son, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me where your father is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.74,0:08:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.07,0:08:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something terrible will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.49,0:08:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know where your father is, don't you, Mr. Lipsky?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You modeled that doll after Nina, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina was the one who told me that you'd be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina did?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.89,0:09:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.39,0:09:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,leave the curtains open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.10,0:09:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.39,0:09:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long have I been here like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.02,0:09:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should rest some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.90,0:09:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:34.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell, somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.70,0:09:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you've been looking after me all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.45,0:09:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.49,0:09:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.29,0:09:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't think of killing myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.67,0:09:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Reichwein and Dieter should be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.13,0:09:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.72,0:09:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.39,0:10:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gathered a lot of material and were\Nstudying it here, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.85,0:10:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay, so please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.07,0:10:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked some of Prague's former secret police members...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.86,0:10:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and some of General Wolf's men...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.95,0:10:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to obtain as much information as they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.08,0:10:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.33,0:10:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a man who's full of mysteries...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm starting to piece together his profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Czechoslovakian born in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.34,0:10:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the name "Franz Bonaparta" is fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.92,0:10:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After World War II...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.51,0:10:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even though numerous Czechs born in Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.47,0:10:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were chased from their homeland of Bohemia...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.72,0:10:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nhis family remained in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under the communist rule in Czechoslovakia...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.02,0:10:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's unclear what kind of role\Nhe played in the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.28,0:10:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I discovered that he married a Czech woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.53,0:10:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even had a son with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.78,0:11:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that his son was actually one of the students...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.37,0:11:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at his book reading seminars...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that began in the mid 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.59,0:11:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Bonaparta's son is in Prague."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.67,0:11:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek's last words...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were pointing to his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it was an old photograph...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to obtain a copy of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.02,0:11:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nshowing all the children who attended\Nthe book readings in the 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.35,0:11:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that this child on the far left is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Not a superior child."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.99,0:11:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was kicked out of the book readings...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.99,0:11:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because he wasn't a "superior child."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He became an "unwanted child" to Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.45,0:11:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure he's the man I know in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.75,0:11:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he know where his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.88,0:11:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he know where Bonaparta is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.55,0:11:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.05,0:12:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's our only clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to hurry, or something terrible will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.81,0:12:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.22,0:12:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.56,0:12:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what Johan is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.23,0:12:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.19,0:12:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The perfect suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.61,0:12:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.69,0:12:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His only expression of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.40,0:12:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,many innocent people will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your bookshelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.04,0:12:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's full of picture books written\Nby Bonaparta under pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've read most of them, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.59,0:12:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After reading several of these, I've\Ncome to realize something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.80,0:12:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the characters in his works have\NGerman names for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe's "The God of Peace."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.52,0:12:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.27,0:12:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the problem is with this pen name, Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.61,0:12:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name Franz Bonaparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and all his other pen names were Czech...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.74,0:13:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but only this pen name was German.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.66,0:13:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe is the real name of your\NGerman-born Czechoslovakian father?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.34,0:13:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a detective using the same reasoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.42,0:13:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who also discovered my father's real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.84,0:13:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was Inspector Lunge from the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.51,0:13:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lunge?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.72,0:13:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.18,0:13:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He left weeks ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.77,0:13:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.06,0:13:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He also made another deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.35,0:13:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, with Inspector Lunge...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.73,0:13:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was more like he became the person\Nrather than using deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am Klaus Poppe."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I have no place to return to."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.66,0:13:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In order to regain tranquility in my heart..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.95,0:13:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I must return to my heart's homeland."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.79,0:13:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,German-born Czechoslovakians\Nwere chased out of Bohemia...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and lost their homeland when Germany lost the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:13:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What part of Germany was his family from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.25,0:14:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.13,0:14:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, my father told me once when I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.68,0:14:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our hometown was in southern Germany,\Nsurrounded by mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.52,0:14:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want that thing anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.48,0:14:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I gave it to Inspector Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.48,0:14:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a postcard I received about three or four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.82,0:14:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sender didn't put his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It had a hand-drawn scene looking down\Non a town from a mountain...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.78,0:14:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,signed by K. P.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.57,0:14:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K. P.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.54,0:14:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.00,0:14:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Southern Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.71,0:14:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A town surrounded by mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.34,0:14:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.88,0:14:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will my father be killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.05,0:14:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.88,0:14:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that won't be the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.76,0:14:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.18,0:14:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is she safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.26,0:14:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make a happy ending for this puppet show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:14:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please protect Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.06,0:14:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, exactly, is about to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.94,0:15:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.28,0:15:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan is trying to recreate it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The massacre that occurred at the Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The slaughter at Kinderheim 511...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.04,0:15:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.08,0:15:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.62,0:15:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,come back alive, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.46,0:15:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.38,0:15:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you must...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.14,0:15:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,starting to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.70,0:15:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alcohol...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.87,0:15:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me some alcohol...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.29,0:15:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.83,0:16:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the police find Mr. Konrad's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.80,0:16:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.67,0:16:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They still have him listed as missing,\Nand they're looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.93,0:16:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew we shouldn't have hidden his body in the woods!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.22,0:16:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we had notified the police right away, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.26,0:16:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the use of saying that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.14,0:16:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You thought I was the one who shot him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.10,0:16:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, this is what we get for winning the lottery
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.23,0:16:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, you didn't need to buy these.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.12,0:16:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train won't come, no matter how long you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.24,0:16:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the rails are flooded because of the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.25,0:16:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Road traffic has also stopped because the river is flooding.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.34,0:16:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we're like a deserted island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.30,0:16:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the worst possible situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.97,0:16:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.30,0:16:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jakub Farobek...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.10,0:16:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emit Sebe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think they and Poppe are all the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.48,0:17:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He changed his art style and content for each...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.94,0:17:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you become an obsessive\Nlike me, you can tell these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I don't know why he used\Nso many different pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.07,0:17:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I find the art interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.74,0:17:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I just can't bring myself to like this person's works.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.37,0:17:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are tons of picture books with\Ndepressing content in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.75,0:17:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But his works are different from those, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are they different?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.76,0:17:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you could say that they are full of malice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.39,0:17:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.98,0:17:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a picture book written by\Nan author named Helmuth Voss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.44,0:17:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was published in 1989.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.94,0:17:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to come by since a very limited number\Nwere printed, but from what I can tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this author and Klaus Poppe are the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.24,0:17:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.54,0:18:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.66,0:18:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell these things when you become like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.66,0:18:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much he changes his art style,\Nit always peeks through somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.09,0:18:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The content has completely changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.88,0:18:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A thief escapes to a town in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.30,0:18:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thief has a scheme to make\Nsome money in that town...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but forgets how to steal after interacting\Nwith the townspeople.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.93,0:18:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.02,0:18:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he lives quietly, working for the people of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.56,0:18:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The title is "A Peaceful Home."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.69,0:18:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those bad feelings you get from his\Npast works were completely gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.03,0:18:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, his art style became much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.49,0:18:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.49,0:18:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When his content became better,\Nhe couldn't draw anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like he lost his goal or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.42,0:18:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A Peaceful Home"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.34,0:18:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A town in the mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.67,0:18:57.88,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Our hometown was in southern Germany,\Nsurrounded by mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.05,0:19:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A map...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.02,0:19:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a map of southern Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.69,0:19:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.81,0:19:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A town in the mountains in southern Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.48,0:19:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruhenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.80,0:19:23.14,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(353,364)}Ruhenheim \N (A Peaceful Home)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.91,0:19:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, it's pouring out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.21,0:19:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, did you find Konrad?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.34,0:19:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I have no idea where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.59,0:19:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My colleagues are still searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.30,0:19:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's difficult in this rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.05,0:19:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rails and roads have been closed\Nbecause the rivers are flooding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.22,0:19:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As his friend, I know you must be worried about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.19,0:19:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, what is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.06,0:19:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to this peaceful town?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Starting with Mr. Konrad's disappearance...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.94,0:19:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Hillman's dog was also shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.70,0:20:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor Mrs. Hillman is bedridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.24,0:20:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kemner was attacked last night\Nright after leaving the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.87,0:20:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he was seriously injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.79,0:20:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't know who attacked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.38,0:20:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Mr. Kemner passes away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.67,0:20:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it will be the first murder since this town was founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.30,0:20:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we have a situation here, no reinforcements\Nare coming because of the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.22,0:20:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we supposed to do with so few men?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.39,0:20:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be outsiders! Outsiders!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.72,0:20:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no crimes in this town before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be the work of outsiders!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.31,0:20:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're outsiders as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.07,0:20:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you guys are...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is pouring out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.95,0:20:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even go outside in this rain with this wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.79,0:20:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get my partner and make one more round.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.08,0:20:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.84,0:21:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband's shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are rather dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if he was walking in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.77,0:21:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm using the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.95,0:21:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that drunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.33,0:21:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like he's going to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.81,0:21:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.93,0:21:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out of gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.77,0:21:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you have an oil leak?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.02,0:21:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could call a mechanic for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.49,0:22:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.62,0:22:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lines are down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.17,0:22:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we can no longer stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.91,0:22:31.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,471)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:44.51,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:44.51,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.51,0:22:47.47,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:23:01.15,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:23:01.15,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:26.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.01,0:23:34.43,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.43,0:23:36.89,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
